Package: aardl
Type: Package
Title: Augmented ARDL Cointegration Analysis
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("Muhammad", "Alkhalaf", email = "muhammedalkhalaf@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0002-2677-9246"))
Description: Implements the Augmented Autoregressive Distributed Lag (A-ARDL)
    bounds cointegration framework of Sam, McNown and Goh (2019)
    <doi:10.1016/j.econlet.2018.12.007>. The package provides eight model
    variants: standard ARDL, bootstrap ARDL following McNown, Sam and Goh
    (2018) <doi:10.1080/00036846.2017.1366150> and Bertelli, Vacca and Zoia
    (2022) <doi:10.1016/j.econlet.2022.110662>, Fourier ARDL following
    Yilanci, Bozoklu and Gorus (2020) <doi:10.1080/1540496X.2019.1594204>,
    and their nonlinear (NARDL) counterparts following Shin, Yu and
    Greenwood-Nimmo (2014) <doi:10.1007/978-1-4899-8008-3_9>. The augmented
    three-test framework (F-overall, t-DV, F-independent) resolves the
    degenerate cases of the standard ARDL bounds test. Lag selection is via
    AIC or BIC.
